Java CC Newsletter 2019 WEEK 34
 
 
 

Steaming Cup of Coffee

 
 
 

JEP 358 Improved NullPointerExceptions 

No matter how carefully they wrote their program, nearly every developer knows the dreaded NullPointerException all too well. The JVM points to the location of the problem, but not in as much detail as you might like.
With JEP 358, Goetz Lindemaier and Ralf Schmelter propose a solution to this problem.

 
 
 
 
 

Draft JEP to Remove Deprecated CMS Garbage Collector

Now that the garbage-first (G1) GC algorithm has been made default in recent versions and with the arrival of fully concurrent modern GC like Oracle-provided ZGC and Red Hat-provided Shenandoah, CMS has become a maintainenance overhead and has been recently deprecated. This JEP draft proposes to fully remove CMS in future JDK versions.

 
 
 
 
 
 

Time to Upgrade 

 
 
 
 
 
 

Spring Framework 5.2 RC2

Spring Framework 5.2 should be avilable in less than a month and it will introduce RSocket support, functional controllers registration in WebMVC, reactive transactions management, support for Kotlin coroutines in WebFlux and Kotlin DSL for various configurations. Follow the link to see the full list of updates

Pragmatism Applied: Avoid Single Implementation Interface

A long time ago (think 2000), all classes in Java used to have an interface. This caused a lot of boilerplating and debugging annoyance. Nowadays with modern frameworks and libraries you do not need interfaces anymore in case of a single implementation. Lets see the reasons behind this statemenet.

From Monolith to Observable Microservices Using DDD

In this talk, Mara Gmez will show you how to move from a monolith to Microservices applying Domain-Driven Design principles. Additionally, she explains how to better maintain Microservices in production by making them observable.

Hibernate Tip: Many-to-Many Association with Additional Attributes

Modeling a many-to-many associations in your table model requires an association table, that references the primary keys of the associated records. If you want to store any additional information for this relationship, you can do that by adding columns to the association table.
See what is the easiest way to map this with Hibernate.

Adding Swagger to Spring Boot

In this article, we'll dive into the Swagger framework. Utilizing Swagger's tools, you can generate code based on the documentation of an API, as well as create beautiful, interactive documentation. This both saves time and effort and offers a standard for people to work with. We will explore ways to visualize and customize Swaggers output. And finally, we will look at a simple OAuth configuration for Swagger.

 
 
 
 
 

Spring Reactive Programming in Java

Reactive programming is a programming paradigm that promotes an asynchronous, non-blocking, event-driven approach to data processing. In the reactive style of programming, we make a request for the resource and start performing other things. Now the question arises: How can we make the Java application in a reactive way. And the answer is using Spring Webflux for which you can learn more in this article.
